posts.title: Melbourne Cup 2017: Revellers make way home as day draws to close | Herald Sun
posts.text:
Use keywords to search content on this website Search Use keywords to search content on this website Melbourne Cup day winners 3:00 
Aaron Langmaid found the winners who backed Rekindling after the running of the 2017 Melbourne Cup November 7th 2017 /display/heraldsun.com.au/Web/HeraldSun/HS State News and Galleries/ Melbourne Cup day winners Melbourne Cup 2017: Pro-refugee protesters scale crane, park car across rail tracks in race hijack bid Wes Hosking, Herald Sun November 7, 2017 7:02pm 
POLICE say Melbourne Cup racegoers have been mostly well-behaved despite a pro-refugee protester bid to hijack the event. 
By about 5pm security had evicted three racegoers for general offending and four for drunkenness. 
Police also made two arrests for drunkenness. 
But the mood was mostly jovial as the day drew to a close. media_camera Racegoers wrestle after the Melbourne Cup. Picture: AAP/Tracey Nearmy media_camera Racegoers arm-wrestle as Melbourne Cup day draws to a close. Picture: AAP/Tracey Nearmy media_camera Racegoers dance at the end of Melbourne Cup day. Picture: AAP/Tracey Nearmy media_camera Racegoers enjoy themselves after the running of the Melbourne Cup. Picture: AAP/Joe Castro media_camera Melbourne Cup day draws to a close at Flemington. Picture: Nicole Garmston 
Earlier, pro-refugee protesters scaled a crane and parked a car across rail tracks in a dangerous bid to hijack the Melbourne Cup. 
Desperate racegoers resorted to walking to Flemington Racecourse after the car — plastered in slogans about Manus Island and animal welfare — suspended services for more than an hour. 
Authorities branded the act incredibly dangerous. 
A woman allegedly bolted to the car was arrested. media_camera Protesters park a car on the railway line near Ascot Vale Rd in Flemington. Picture: Andrew Tauber 
Supt Tim Hansen said: "It's a really dangerous situation that certainly inconvenienced the broader public." 
"Leaving a vehicle on a railway track has a whole lot of implications around safety and it's not something we would like to see again,'' Supt Hansen said. 
"Fortunately no trains were involved in a collision." 
The car blocked the tracks at a level crossing between Ascot Vale Rd and Newmarket railway station just before 1.15pm, forcing services to and from Flemington to be suspended. 
About 20 protesters at the scene fled. 
MFB crews were needed to remove the arrested woman, a 27-year-old from Moonee Ponds, because she was bolted to the car's steering wheel. The vehicle's tyres had been let down. media_camera Manus Island protesters on a construction crane at Flemington. Picture: AAP/James Ross 
The woman was assisting police and facing charges including reckless conduct endangering life, careless driving and unlicensed driving. 
A Flemington-bound train carrying 172 people was forced to stop as a result of the incident — some 55 passengers forcing the carriage doors open. Some walked to Flemington in their determination to see the Cup while taxis and Ubers were stretched. 
The train returned to Newmarket about 2pm. 
"I understand where they are coming from however there are better ways to approach this situation," one racegoer said of the protesters. 
"Parking a car on the train line does not only endanger their lives it endangers everybody around them, including the police. It puts everyone's lives in danger. 
“Just put a petition against the government like everyone else does." 
Metro Trains spokeswoman Sammie Black said the car drama caused major disruptions, with passengers forcing the doors posing a "significant safety risk". 
Train services resumed at about 2.30pm — just in time for the post-Cup crowd stampede. 
Earlier, about 12.45pm, two women protesters unveiled a huge banner on a crane above Flemington. media_camera Protesters Kat and Hannah atop of a crane overlooking the Flemington racecourse. Picture: Supplied 
They later agreed to come down and were likely to face charges including breaches of work safety laws. 
Police also arrested one woman and were hunting two others after a man protesting against horse racing was allegedly assaulted and had his protest banner damaged at Epsom Rd about 9.30am.

Press Release

*Bastei Lübbe AG: Unplanned write-down at subsidiary oolipo AG burdens the result in the second quarter*

*Cologne, 7 November 2017. *Bastei Lübbe AG (ISIN DE000A1X3YY0) announces that - *oolipo* - the streaming platform for reading content, developed with considerable financial efforts, has far from reached the expected and necessary user numbers until the present day. At the same time, the search for new investors to drive forward the needed further development of the platform has been unsuccessful up to now. Upon agreement with the Supervisory Board, the Management Board of Bastei Lübbe AG, therefore, decided not to invest any further funds into the project and to undertake an unscheduled write-down.

The non-cash write-down on the intangible assets of its subsidiary oolipo AG will extraordinarily impact the consolidated EBIT of the Group in the second quarter of the current financial year in the amount of approximately EUR 3 million. Over the next months, the Management Board will consider the possibility of differently using or exploiting the developed technology.

The Management Board team of Bastei Lübbe AG, led by CEO Carel Halff, will consider the strategic direction of the Group in detail over the coming months, focusing on operational opportunities and risks, and adapt or refine the business strategy in close agreement with the Supervisory Board.

About Bastei Lübbe AG:

Bastei Lübbe AG is an internationally active media group with headquarters in Cologne. Its business activities primarily focus on the development and licencing of contents which are sold worldwide in physical and digital formats. The core business of the company in the book segment covers classic publishing and periodically published puzzle magazines and novels. With its total of twelve publishing houses and imprints, the company group currently offers around 3,600 titles in the areas of fiction, non-fiction as well as books for children and young adults. In the growing segment of hardcover fiction books, the company has been the market leader in Germany for many years. At the same time, Bastei Lübbe is an engine for innovation in the area of digital media. Apart from the production of thousands of audio and ebooks, the "digital" business unit also maintains participations in the self-publishing platform "BookRix" and the renowned game publisher "Daedalic Entertainment". The digital value-added chain of Bastei Lübbe AG is rounded off through its participation in the online shop "beam-ebooks.de".

With annual sales of approx. 146.3 million euros (financial year 2016/2017), Bastei Lübbe AG is the largest medium-sized family-run publishing business in Germany. The shares of the company have been listed in the Prime Standard segment on the Frankfurt stock exchange (GSIN A1X3YY, ISIN DE000A1X3YY0) since 2013. Further information is available at www.luebbe.de.

Who were the Texas church shooting victims? Here's what we know about the people who died By: RALPH ELLIS Posted: Nov 07, 2017 12:12 AM CST Updated: Nov 07, 2017 03:04 AM CST Texas church shooting: What happened 
(CNN) - Many of them had known each other for years. That's no surprise in a small town like Sutherland Springs, Texas, where lives intersect daily on the street, at the school and in the church. 
Twenty-six of those lives ended Sunday when Devin Kelley walked into the First Baptist Church of Sutherland Springs with an assault rifle. 
Law enforcement has not released the identities of any of the people killed, but family members have come forward with details and photos of their slain loved ones. 
Here's what we know so far about the people who died. Lula White 
She was grandmother to Devin Kelley's wife. 
White volunteered frequently at the church, according to friends and her Facebook profile. 
"I have no doubt where she is right now. She is in heaven laying her crowns and jewels at the feet of Jesus and celebrating. I love and will miss you Aunt Lula Woicinski White," niece Amy Backus wrote on Facebook. 
Another family member, Charity Sales, posted to Facebook, "Aunt Lula Woicinski White will be missed greatly, I don't think there was ever a time I saw her she didn't have a smile on her face and a crazy fun tactic up her sleeve." Annabelle Pomeroy 
She was the 14-year-old daughter of Sherri and Frank Pomeroy, the church's regular pastor who was traveling when the shooting occurred. 
"We lost more than Belle yesterday, and the one thing that gives me a sliver of encouragement is the fact that Belle was surrounded by her church family that she loved fiercely, and vice versa," Sherri Pomeroy said. 
"We ate together, we laughed together, we cried together, and we worshiped together. Now most of our church family is gone, our building is probably beyond repair and the few of us that are left behind lost tragically yesterday. 
"As senseless as this tragedy was, our sweet Belle would not have been able to deal with losing so much family." 
In one sermon posted online, Frank Pomeroy, who rode a motorcycle, spoke about riding with his daughter. Haley Krueger 
The 16-year-old had helped with breakfast that morning at the church, said her mother, Charlene Marie Uhl. 
Haley loved babies and looked forward to a career as a nurse in a neonatal intensive care unit, she said. She loved attending the Baptist church in Sutherland Springs. 
"She was a vibrant 16-year-old that loved life," her mother said. The Holcombes 
Eight members of the Holcombe family died in the shooting. 
Bryan Holcombe was serving as guest pastor on Sunday. He lived on a farm in nearby Floresville with his wife, Karla Holcombe, said Ron Scott, a cousin to the Holcombe family. Karla Holcombe was also killed. 
The others in the family who died were Danny Holcombe, Bryan and Karla Holcombe's son; Noah Holcombe, Danny's 17-month-old daughter; Crystal Holcombe, the pregnant wife of Bryan and Karla's other son, John, who survived the shooting; and three of Crystal Holcombe's five children, Emily Hill, Megan Hill and Evelin Hill, to whom John Holcombe was stepfather. 
Authorities have included Crystal Holcombe's unborn child in the death count. 
Two of her children survived and are in the hospital with John Holcombe. 
Tara Elyse Mcnulty also died. She was a close friend of the family, lived with Bryan and Karla and called them Mom and Dad, Ron Scott said. Richard and Theresa Rodriguez 
Richard and Theresa had been married for 11 years, and had been members of the church for "many years," according to Richard's daughter Regina. She says her dad and step-mom were very active in the church. 
"If they weren't at church they were always in their yard working on their garden beds or cutting the grass," Regina said. 
"He loved music. My favorite memories was waking up on a Saturday morning and watching "Soul Train" with him, and 80s movies." Robert and Shani Corrigan 
Originally from Harrison, Michigan, Robert and Shandi Corrigan had moved to Texas, where they became part of the praise team at the Sutherland Springs church. 
Robert had served in the Air Force for 30 years. He was a track star in high school and valedictorian of his class, according to CNN affiliate WWTV. 
The high school sweethearts got married in 1985, after graduation. 
Their son, Forrest, died last year, and the pastor at the First Baptist Church officiated the funeral. 
Robert, known to those who loved him as Bobby, "loved life, everything he did was to the extreme," his uncle, Bob Sommers told WWTV. "He was a pleasure to be around." 
As members of the Harrison community gathered to remember the victims, Robert's mother, Jean-Anne Corrigan told CNN affiliate WDIV that she believes that both Robert and his wife are in heaven.

Итог российской революции 1917 года губителен как минимум с трех точек зрения, считает историк. "Для России эта революция стала катастрофой. Спровоцировав страшную гражданскую войну, Ленин начиная с 1922 года привел к экономической разрухе страну, которая была мировым лидером по производству зерна и нефти, а также мощной промышленной державой. Он возглавил свою партию-государство и во имя радикальной марксистской идеологии запретил частную собственность и частную торговлю, разорил имущие классы. Он истребил или вынудил бежать значительную часть интеллектуальной, научной, технической и предпринимательской элит. Он ограбил крестьянство - вызвав множество бунтов - и решительно обуздал рабочий класс", - пишет Куртуа. Ленин "создал гигантское количество чиновников, набранных по принципу верности режиму, а не благодаря своей компетенции", продолжает историк. "А главное, он разогнал Учредительное собрание - вплоть до 1991 года первый и последний орган, избранный в России всеобщим голосованием", - говорится в статье. "Сразу же после этого он создал всемогущую политическую полицию и Красную армию, уполномоченные истреблять всех, кто выступал против его режима. Он включил в повестку дня террор", - пишет автор. "Второе губительное наследие касается Европы. Своими нескончаемыми выпадами против Веймарской республики и немецкой социал-демократии Ленин и Сталин в значительной степени облегчили приход к власти Гитлера в 1933 году; а агрессивные советско-нацистские пакт и договор от 23 и 28 сентября 1939 года дали сигнал к началу Второй мировой со всеми ее трагическими последствиями: геноцид евреев и цыган, миллионы погибших в боях и под бомбежками, и прочее, и прочее. Дороже всех заплатила Россия: 27 млн погибших. А после 1945 года Центральную и Восточную Европу ждало "освобождение" силами Красной армии и советизация, с которой удалось покончить лишь в 1989 году", - пишет Куртуа. "Третье наследие затрагивает весь мир, - считает историк. - По сути, Ленин изобрел новый тип диктатуры - тоталитаризм, который претендует на контроль не только над политической властью, но и над всем обществом, вплоть до отдельного индивида и его образа мыслей. И СССР, посредством сети компартий, распространил этот тоталитаризм в Европе и Азии - со всеми ужасами Мао в Китае и Пол Пота в Камбодже - не говоря уж о Кубе и отдельных африканских режимах". "Падение Берлинской стены в 1989 году, затем развал СССР в 1991-м стали следствием полного провала ленинской авантюры. Однако с тех пор тоталитаризм перекочевал от умирающего коммунизма к торжествующему исламскому радикализму", - заключает Куртуа. Источник: Ouest-France

WABTEC Quality Director - Electronics in Wilmerding , Pennsylvania 
Overview 
The Quality Director- Electronics will provide leadership and expertise in assertively driving performance improvements in the Electronics Group Quality performance while establishing and implementing effective corporate quality assurance methodologies that monitor, improve, control, and maintain quality products and processes for Wabtec and its suppliers. 
Responsibilities 
Provide strategic leadership, management and direction to Quality Assurance Team 
Establish and maintain Group Quality Management System (QMS) and ensure compliance with ISO 9001 and IRIS standards. 
Evaluate the effectiveness and efficiency of the Software Development Process in meeting the customer and business requirements 
Assist the business units in maintaining and assessing Quality Certifications including ISO, AAR, IRIS 
Ensure QA team is evaluating the process compliances and providing visibility on process compliance 
Develop and implement quality metrics associated with Electronic and software design development 
Establish Process Performance Baselines and set Quality Improvement goals for each business unit 
Monitor and measure Process Performance Measure against the set goals and initiate corrective actions as appropriate 
Monitor Electronics Group business performance through KPI’s and the progression of the Wabtec Excellence Program. 
Assist the business units in driving improvements to their performance while reducing quality costs. 
Participate in continuous improvement processes, such as Kaizen and statistical engineering programs. 
Through the use of statistical methods and data analysis, studies variation in product and process quality and assists the business unit in understanding the nature and causes of variation. 
Perform supplier process audits as needed including China, India, Europe, and North America, which will require a minimum 30% travel. 
Hold periodic Group conferences to share best practices and ensure accountability to Wabtec Quality requirements. 
Qualifications 
Minimum education, job experience, certifications, and skills: 
BS: Engineering or related field (minimum required) 
Comprehensive knowledge the Software Quality Assurance concepts and techniques 
In depth knowledge of ISO, IRIS and CMMI Standards / models 
10 + years of work experience, Quality Assurance program in an electronics and software design and development environment 
Understanding of continuous improvement and lean manufacturing concepts 
Ability to conduct process capabilities studies, SPC and other assurance engineering studies 
Proficient in the use of computers 
Specialized equipment used in this job: 
Computer and office equipment 
Minitab Statistical Analysis Software (Preferred) 
Other skills and qualifications 
Experience in Agile Scrum Mythology is a plus 
Excellent verbal and written communication/language skills required to include the ability to provide written and verbal instructions, compile and present business reports/correspondence, and present information clearly. 
Experience with Electronics Design and Developments process 
Experience with Advanced Product Quality Planning (APQP). 
Excellent analytical and reasoning ability for solving problems and good judgment for decision-making. 
Capable of planning and organizing work and processes; ability to self-direct multiple projects and meet deadlines. 
Ability to cooperate and interpersonal skills to work effectively as a team member. 
Quality orientation. 
Motivation to provide excellent internal and external customer service 
Job LocationsUS-PA-Wilmerding

posts.text: Ε.Π.Κ.Κρήτης "Διαστάσεις χιονοστιβάδας, οι καταγγελίες για ελαττωματικά κινητά τηλέφωνα" Με αφορμή το πλήθος των καταγγελιών , που φθάνουν τις τελευταίες ημέρες στην ΄Ενωση Προστασίας Καταναλωτών Κρήτης για προβληματικές συσκευές κινητών τηλεφώνων, από καταναλωτές , "θύματα" εμπορικών πρακτιών, η ΄Ενωση οφείλει να ενημερώσει τους καταναλωτές ότι, έχουν δικαιώματα και μετά την αγορά του προϊόντος (τηλεφωνικής συσκευής κινητού) και οφείλουν να τα διεκδικήσουν , αφενός ως πρώτο βήμα να απευθυνθούν στο κατάστημα αγοράς της συσκευής κινητού τηλεφώνου, διεκδικώντας τα νόμιμα δικαιώματα τους , και εάν αντιμετωπίσουν αρνητική στάση του καταστήματος , να το καταγγείλουν, απευθυνόμενοι είτε στο 1520 (Γενική Γραμματεία Καταναλωτή ), είτε σε Πιστοποιημένη ΄Ενωση Καταναλωτών, της περιοχής τους. Δικαιώματα του καταναλωτή 1. Να απαιτήσει, χωρίς επιβάρυνσή του, τη διόρθωση ή αντικατάσταση του πράγματος με άλλο, η οποία θα πρέπει να πραγματοποιηθεί σε εύλογο χρόνο, εκτός αν μια τέτοια ενέργεια είναι αδύνατη ή απαιτεί δυσανάλογες δαπάνες ή 2. Να μειώσει το τίμημα ή 3. Να υπαναχωρήσει από τη σύμβαση (δηλαδή να επιστρέψει το προϊόν και να ζητήσει τα χρήματά του πίσω), εκτός αν πρόκειται για επουσιώδες πραγματικό ελάττωμα. Μάλιστα, η άσκηση των σχετικών δικαιωμάτων μπορεί να γίνει μέσα σε δύο (2) έτη από την ημέρα της πώλησης, όταν και παραγράφονται, σύμφωνα με το άρθρο 554 ΑΚ. Δηλαδή , πρακτικά, ο καταναλωτής που αγοράζει ένα κινητό τηλέφωνο ή άλλη συσκευή τεχνολογίας αιχμής, δικαιούται μέχρι και 2 έτη μετά την αγορά τους, να ασκήσει τα παραπάνω δικαιώματά του κατά του πωλητή, εφόσον το αντικείμενο που αγόρασε παρουσιάζει συγκεκριμένο πραγματικό ελάττωμα ή έλλειψη συνομολογημένης ιδιότητας υπαιτιότητας όχι του ίδιου του καταναλωτή αλλά του πωλητή, ανεξάρτητα από την διάρκεια εγγύησης που δίνει η κατασκευάστρια εταιρεία. Οοσίας, τεκμαίρεται εκ του Νόμου ότι, το πραγματικό ελάττωμα ή η έλλειψη συνομολογημένης ιδιότητας υφίσταται αν παρουσιαστεί μέσα σε ένα εξάμηνο από τον χρόνο της πώλησης, ενώ από τον έβδομο μήνα και μετά θα πρέπει να αποδειχθεί η ύπαρξή της. Περαιτέρω , καθησυχάζομαι τους καταναλωτές οι οποίοι ταλαιπωρούνται μήνες ,από τις υποσχέσεις των καταστημάτων ότι θα τους επισκευάσουν την συσκευή - κινητό ,ότι έχουν το δικαίωμα να προβούν άμεσα σε καταγγελίες στην Ένωση Προστασίας Καταναλωτών Κρήτης, καθώς δεν αποκλείεται, υπό προϋποθέσεις, να οδηγηθούμε σε δικαστική αξίωση εις όφελος του καταναλωτή-αγοραστή για αποζημίωσή του από τον πωλητή. Τέλος ,ως Ένωση των Καταναλωτών,που μέσα στους βασικούς σκοπούς της είναι η προστασία των συμφερόντων (οικονομικών και άλλων)των καταναλωτών,υπενθυμίζουμε στους πωλητές- καταστημάτων συσκευών κινητής τηλεφωνίας, να βάλουν ένα στοπ ,σε πρακτικές μη νόμιμες, καθώς ο μη σεβασμός των νομοθετημένων δικαιωμάτων των καταναλωτών ,οδηγεί σε μονόδρομο της Δικαιοσύνης. Για καταχρηστικές πρακτικές ,για τις συσκευές κινητών τηλεφώνων , επικοινωνήστε με το 1520 ή στα τηλ. της ΄Ενωσης 2821092306 και 2821092666 Η Πρόεδρος της ΄Ένωσης Προστασίας Καταναλωτών Κρήτης Ιωάννα Μελάκη

posts.title: xml 파일로 불러오는 방법
posts.text: 프로그래밍 xml 파일로 불러오는 방법 1시간 전 URL 복사 본문 기타 기능 번역보기 http://blog.naver.com/gkswndks123/221134701287 **ViewResolver => Controller가 리턴한 뷰 이름을 가지고 실제 출력할 뷰의 종류와 뷰 파일의 이름을 결정하기 위한 클래스 1. InternalResourceViewResolver => html이나 jsp를 이용해서 출력할 때 사용하는 뷰 리졸버 => prefix 프로퍼티와 suffix 프로퍼티를 이용해서 공통되는 부분을 설정할 수 있습니다. 2. BeanNameViewResolver => html이나 jsp를 제외한 형태의 뷰로 출력할 때 사용하는 뷰 리졸버 => 뷰 지졸버를 만들고 뷰 이름에 해당하는 뷰 클래스를 직접 설정해서 출력 3. 2개의 혼합사용 => order 프로퍼티를 이용해서 실행순서를 결정해주어야 하는데 InternalResourceViewResolver가 후위 순위를 가져야 합니다. ** 엑셀로 출력하기 => apache poi 라이브러리를 이용하고 AbstractExcelView 클래스로부터 상속받는 클래스를 이용합니다. => 이 때 주의할 점은 요청 주소가 엑셀 파일의 이름이 되기 때문에 요청 주소에 엑셀파일의 확장자를 붙여주는 것이 좋습니다. 1. po m.xml 파일에 poi 라이브러리 의존성을 추가합니다. org.apache.poi poi 3.16 2. home.jsp에 요청하는 것을 만들기 [엑셀로출력] 3. HomeController 에 요청을 처리하는 메소드를 생성해서 처리 @RequestMapping(value="excel.xls", method=RequestMethod.GET) public String excel(Model model) { //데이터 가져오기 List list = itemService.getList(); //데이터 저장 model.addAttribute("list", list); return "excel"; } 4. 위의 데이터를 출력할 AbstractExcelView로 부터 상속받는 View 클래스를 생성 =>kr.co.pk.view.ExcelView 5. servlet-context.xml 파일에서 Controller에서 exel로 출력해달라는 요청이오면 ExcellView로 출력할 수 있도록 설정을 추가 1)InternalResourceViewResolver의 출력 순서를 조정 2) 뷰 이름을 가지고 출력할 뷰를 선택할 수 있도록 해주는 BeanNameViewResolver 설정을 추가 3) 엑셀로 출력해주는 요청에서 리턴한 뷰 이름과 엑셀 뷰를 매핑시키는 코드를 추가 **PDF 파일 출력 => 보고서나 E-Book에 많이 사용하는 포맷 => i text API를 이용해서 구현 => http://itextpdf.com/product 사이트에 가면 java 와 C #코드를 제공합니다. => WEB에서는 AbtractPdfView로 부터 상속받는 클래스를 이용해서 출력합니다. 1. po m.xml 파일에 itext 라이브러리의 의존성을 설정 2. home.jsp 파일에 pdf로 출력하는 요청을 생성 [pdf로 출력] 3. HomeController에 요청을 처리하는 메소드를 생성 @RequestMapping(value="pdf", method=RequestMethod.GET) public String pdf(Model model) { //데이터 가져오기 Listlist = itemService.getList(); //데이터 저장하기 model.addAttribute("list", list); return "pdfview"; } 4. AbstractPdfView로 부터 상속받는 클래스를 만들고 데이터를 출력하는 코드를 작성 - kr.co.pk.view.Pdfview ** 프로젝트에 데이터 삽입 기능을 추가 1. home.jsp 파일에 데이터 삽입 링크를 추가 상품등록 2. HomeController 클래스에 insert 요청이 왔을 때 호출되는 메소드를 작성 @RequestMapping(value="insert", method=RequestMethod.GET) public String insert(Model model) { return "insert"; } 3. views 디렉토리에 insert.jsp를 만들고 데이터 삽입 화면을 작성

posts.text:
WABTEC Shipping & Receiving Team Leader in Buffalo Grove , Illinois 
Overview 
Vapor Bus International is a division of Wabtec Corporation and is the principal door equipment supplier to the North American bus industry. A broad range of products is available for transit and commuter buses, intercity and tour coaches, and utility vehicles. The company offers complete automatic door systems as well as individual components such as actuators, door controls, door panels, seals, and door accessories. Both pneumatic and electric actuators are available. Control options range from simple electro-mechanical devices to high-capability, microprocessor-based systems. Vapor maintains strong relationships with transit properties throughout the U.S. and Canada and is an active member in the American Public Transportation Association (APTA) and Canadian Urban Transportation Association (CUTA). Vapor strives to understand the needs of the evolving transit industry and to provide products and services that satisfy these needs. Sales and service for Vapor products is provided by representatives located at offices in New York, New York; Buffalo Grove, Illinois; Los Angeles, California; Sacramento, California; Toronto, Ontario; Baltimore, Maryland; Austin, Texas; Manchester, UK, and Sassuolo, Italy. Vapor Bus International is committed to combining the skills and experience of its people with the best equipment and processes to offer world-class solutions for its customers' needs. 
Responsibilities 
Summary: Responsible for a group of people who either assemble, operate small equipment or drive for lifts to produce quality work while maintaining a smooth flow of output which matches customer demand within either a department or a cell.Coordinates and engages in verifying and keeping records on incoming and outgoing shipments, and preparing items for shipment by performing the following duties. 
Provides technical expertise to team members when needed. Problem solves through others or through team input. Develops, releases, and then ensures the team meets the daily schedule. Works with skilled and semi-skilled team members to ensure safety, 5S, continuous improvement, cross training and implementation of other lean manufacturing tools. Total Productivity Maintenance (TPM) may be applicable but would be limited in scope. Instructions are taken from Oracle system, Kanban cards, routers, blueprints and or flat screen, PC spreadsheets, supervisor, manager, and customer service. 
Essential Duties and Responsibilitiesinclude the following. Other duties may be assigned. 
Ensure a safe working environment, good housekeeping and 5’s for your respective area and all of VBI 
Conducts stand-up meeting with team members to discuss safety, quality productivity, TPM, 5S and CIA’s. 
Trains and ensure employees are utilizing proper PPE for each area. 
Recommends measures to improve production methods, equipment performance, and quality of product. 
Established plans to reduce and or eliminate internal and external customer rejects. 
Analyzes and resolves work problems, or assists workers in solving work problems. Identify root cause and implement corrective action. 
Develops and provides input on assembly requirements needed to determine the total material and labor to meet BOM’s and cost targets. 
Setup and maintains Kanban boards to meet the start, due and delivery dates. Studies production schedules and estimates the hours required to complete job assignments. Reviews Kanban cards or other schedules to establish priorities based upon start, due or ship dates. 
Interfaces with other departments to ensure customer order deadlines are met. Maintains 99% or better OTD (on time delivery) performance with internal and external customers 
Creates detailed schedule time lines to ensure customer shipment dates and equipment specifications are met. 
Establishes or adjusts work procedures to meet production schedules 
Develops a process plan including people, resources, equipment, and floor space for each customer order. 
Provides input on machine and cell layout to ensure efficient flow of materials, 
Use equipment and resources to increase efficiency and productivity of shop, department, or work crew. 
Coordinates manpower requirements by increasing or decreasing personnel and overtime to meet changing conditions. 
Maintains time and production records. 
Estimates, requisitions, and inspects materials. 
Confers with other supervisors to coordinate activities of individual departments. 
Reports machine and equipment malfunctions to maintenance personnel. 
Performs activities of workers supervised. 
Able to read and interpret blue prints, BOM’s, Routers and other technical documents 
Interprets company policies to workers and enforces safety regulations. 
Complete training spreadsheet for all new hires. Train employees on the technical aspects of the job. 
Generates recovery plans in case of absences. 
Provides information to supervisor or manager of problems or issues outside of scope of responsibility. 
Creates, presents, and displays Key Performance Indicator reports. Maintains visual factory display boards. 
Actively participates in Kaizen events and continuous improvement activities (CIA’s). 
With team, performs root cause problem solving analysis and completes corrective actions. 
Reviews and assists team members with lessons learned. 
Motivates, coaches and cross-trains members of the team to achieve production goals. 
Studies shipping notices, bills of lading, invoices, orders, and other records to determine shipping priorities, work assignments, and shipping methods required to meet shipping and receiving schedules. Coordinates with other associates as needed. 
Confirm shipments to customers as required by customer instruction. 
Oversees incoming and outgoing shipping activities to ensure accuracy, completeness, and condition of shipments, including customer returns, material, equipment and supplies. 
Determines space requirements and position of shipment containers and trucks and lays out position of shipment for most economical means of delivery to meet customer requirements. 
Inspects loading operations to ensure compliance with shipping specifications and compliance with customer instructions regarding packing, shipping and labeling. This includes audit of order for part and quantity accuracy and pallet count. 
Inspects material handling equipment for defects and notifies maintenance personnel or contacts outside service facility for repair. 
Compiles records of unfilled/back orders for Customer Service. 
Prepares bills of lading, customs and export documents for domestic and international shipments. 
Tracks shipments and obtains proof of deliveries when required. 
Monitors and returns inventory of customer-owned returnable containers. 
Arranges for pickup of scrap metal and trash in the facility. 
Creates computer generated reports relating to shipping and receiving including manifests on a daily basis. 
Communicates with Customer Service and employees in a professional manner at all times. 
Must meet weekly, daily and hourly deadlines for key tasks related to shipping product, and sending EDI information to trucking companies and customers. 
Receive incoming goods, confirm accuracy and route appropriately. 
Qualifications 
Education/Experience: 
Associate's degree (A. A.) or equivalent from two-year College or technical school; 4 to six years related experience and/or training; or equivalent combination of education and experience. Oracle experience a plus, ability to drive fork lifts (stand-up). 
Job LocationsUS-IL-Buffalo Grove

posts.title: The reason for Apple's record profit forecast? Apparently, the iPhone X costs $358 to make
posts.text:
Tags : T-Mobile - T-Mobile + AT&T - AT&T + Verizon - Verizon + Sprint - Sprint + iOS - iOS + Apple - Apple + 
Apple pours in $358 worth of parts in the iPhone X, takes out $999 at retail for a dreamy 64% gross margin " We expect revenue to be between $84 billion and $87 billion ." This simple sentence mentioned on the fly by CEO Tim Cook during a conference call with investors discussing Apple's current quarter forecast , have sent the stock on an upward trajectory since Friday, the day the iPhone X was released. If this revenue number pans out, and Apple is usually conservative with estimates, this will mark the most bountiful quarter for any company... in history. Given the rumors that the iPhone 8 lags in sales compared to the iPhone 7 , and is even overcome by the iPhone 8 Plus , such a rosy outlook might seem premature, but Apple is not one to talk empty words on conference calls, so where is Tim Cook's optimism coming from? Well, from the iPhone X gross margin, it seems. The phone got another teardown over the weekend, and its bill of materials (BoM) estimate is $357.50. Apple can be different here because they are the 800 pound gorilla While quite a bit higher than for most iPhones so far, whose BoM usually hovers in the $200-$250 range, the retail price of the iPhone X is also up there, and returns no less than 64% gross margin for Apple, compared to the iPhone 8's 59%. Needless to say, this doesn't include R&D expenses, or marketing and administrative costs, but these, in the case of Apple, usually stay in the 10-15% range anyway, even for a unique handset like the X. Thus, while the cost of materials to build an iPhone X is 25% higher than for the iPhone 8, its price is 43% higher, so Apple expects the new OLED iPhone to add a big fat chunk to its revenue and profit this quarter, and probably the next few. The priciest part in the iPhone X is the OLED screen, supplied by Samsung, at $65.50 a pop, just as predicted , but Apple also didn't skimp on another important aspect - structural rigidity, as the $36 stainless steel frame costs much more than the iPhone 8's $21.50 aluminum housing, which is made of the highest grade 7-series alloy, but still gives way to the steel frame Apple uses in the iPhone X. Thus, analysts are expecting Apple to pierce through the $100 billion quarterly revenue barrier next year, riding on the wings of the iPhone X and its sucessors' gross margin, and it will be the first company in history to do so, barring any unforeseen troubles with Apple's newest handset.

posts.title: 국내 프로바이오틱스 선도기업인 쎌바이오텍이 3분기 연결재무제표 기준 매출액 156억원, 영
posts.text:
국내 프로바이오틱스 선도기업인 쎌바이오텍이 3분기 연결재무제표 기준 매출액 156억원, 영업이익 60억원, 당기순이익 52억원의 실적(잠정)을 기록했다고 7일 밝혔다. 이는 전년 동기 대비 각각 31.8%, 49.4%, 103.4% 늘어난 실적이다.
쎌바이오텍은 “이번 분기는 추석 특수 등의 영향으로 국내 완제 및 듀오락 매출이 분기 기준 최고치를 달성한 것이 특징”이라며 “꾸준한 원가율 개선과 효율적인 비용관리로 3분기까지 40%의 이익률을 이어가고 있다”고 설명했다.
실제 3분기까지의 누적실적은 두자릿수 성장세를 이어가며 순항 중이다. 누적매출은 476억원, 누적영업이익은 190억원, 누적당기순이익은 156억원으로 전년 대비 각각 10.3%, 11.9%, 16.9% 증가했다.
쎌바이오텍 관계자는 “4분기에 한방용 제품인 듀오락 오리엔탈과 액티브 바이털이 본격적으로 전국 한방병원 및 한의원으로 보급이 확대될 예정”이라며 “올리브영 전용 제품과 스킨플로라(피부균총) 정상화를 돕는 신개념 프로바이오틱스 화장품 라인업이 추가될 예정이어서 실적에 긍정적인 영향을 줄 수 있을 것으로 기대된다”고 말했다.
